text: Plymouth is a city in Sheboygan County, Wisconsin, along the Mullet River. The city is located in the Town of Plymouth, but is politically independent. Plymouth is known as "Hub City" because it is a former regional center of wooden wheelwrighting. The population was 8,932 at the 2020 census. ==References== Category:Cities in Wisconsin Category:Sheboygan County, Wisconsin
